<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B08FFC4FF11F13FF7E6FDDD" pageId="22" pageNumber="533" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B08FFC4FF11F13FFB1BF24E" blockId="22.[132,1338,3406,3482]" pageId="22" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B08FFC4FF11F13FFEB1F2B7" bold="true" box="[133,289,3406,3435]" pageId="22" pageNumber="533">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B08FFC4FEBBF13FFC08F2B7" authority="J. R. Contreras, 1995" authorityName="J. R. Contreras" authorityYear="1995" box="[303,920,3406,3435]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="22" pageNumber="533" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rosendopascuali">Ctenomys rosendopascuali J. R. Contreras, 1995</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="61F1F00F1B08FFC4FC3CF13FFB1BF24E" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798388332" pageId="22" pageNumber="533">“Mar Chiquita, Departamento San Justo, provincia de Cordoba, Argentina, 30°48’ S, 62°53’ W, 65 m.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D126FA521B08FFC4F84CFD6BF5B7FE05" blockId="22.[2008,2602,282,710]" pageId="22" pageNumber="533">According to mtDNA analysis with cytochrome-b, C. rosendopascuali is in the mendocinusspecies group. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 52 and FN = 62, 64, or 66, and sperm is simple asymmetric.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D126FA521B08FFC4F84EFD91F7E6FDDD" blockId="22.[2008,2602,282,710]" box="[2010,2166,480,513]" pageId="22" pageNumber="533">Monotypic.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
